1
00:02:31,960 --> 00:02:34,680
What's she doing at Boss Nok's label?

2
00:02:34,760 --> 00:02:35,600
PREVIOUS EPISODE

3
00:02:35,680 --> 00:02:37,080
Is she switching labels?

4
00:02:37,160 --> 00:02:38,200
Don't worry, Puna.

5
00:02:39,040 --> 00:02:42,720
I'm the director.
I'll guide you to make it work.

6
00:02:43,520 --> 00:02:44,560
No problem at all.

7
00:02:45,320 --> 00:02:49,440
That's right! If Puna shoots
this commercial and becomes famous,

8
00:02:49,960 --> 00:02:51,840
you'll be totally overshadowed.

9
00:02:51,920 --> 00:02:54,440
No, I won't let that happen!

10
00:02:58,240 --> 00:02:59,320
Get in the car.

11
00:03:01,880 --> 00:03:02,960
AGRICULTURAL PRODUCT PROCESSING FACTORY

12
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:05,560
There's definitely something in here.

13
00:03:05,640 --> 00:03:06,240
PROCESSED AGRICULTURAL PRODUCTS

14
00:03:06,320 --> 00:03:07,360
Hey! Don't touch that!

15
00:03:10,200 --> 00:03:12,680
Teacher! Teacher!

16
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:20,840
Lock her up so she stays in there.

17
00:03:20,920 --> 00:03:23,000
Finally, no more thorns!

18
00:03:23,920 --> 00:03:25,480
Alright, time to announce.

19
00:03:25,560 --> 00:03:28,480
Come on out, our commercial star!

20
00:03:28,560 --> 00:03:33,080
-Ta-da!
-Ta-da!

21
00:03:36,120 --> 00:03:39,000
I'm beautiful and look
like a real lead, right?

22
00:03:39,080 --> 00:03:44,040
Miss Maria, you look amazing,
glowing, sparkling, like a diamond!

23
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:46,520
Hurry up, or we'll be late.

24
00:03:47,640 --> 00:03:48,480
I was enjoying my moment!

25
00:03:49,840 --> 00:03:52,320
Can you save that feeling
for Mr. Sonrak at the set?

26
00:03:52,400 --> 00:03:54,480
Exactly! Hurry up. Let's go!

27
00:03:55,600 --> 00:03:57,440
-You're beautiful.
-After you, gorgeous.

28
00:03:57,520 --> 00:03:58,720
Absolutely gorgeous!

29
00:03:58,800 --> 00:03:59,760
Turn around.

30
00:04:09,440 --> 00:04:10,600
Come here, Teacher!

31
00:04:21,720 --> 00:04:24,600
Hurry, Puna. We'll miss
the commercial shoot.

32
00:04:30,320 --> 00:04:32,640
Help! Is anyone out there?

33
00:04:33,680 --> 00:04:37,760
Ugh. Is anyone there? Please help us!

34
00:04:39,360 --> 00:04:40,520
What should we do, Teacher?

35
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:42,440
Looks like it's locked from the outside.

36
00:04:46,320 --> 00:04:47,600
Hey, I know!

37
00:04:48,600 --> 00:04:50,880
-We have to go out this way.
-Which way?

38
00:04:56,120 --> 00:04:58,320
Wait, don't tell me…

39
00:04:58,400 --> 00:05:02,480
There's only one way.
It's the only way we can get out.

40
00:05:04,800 --> 00:05:06,720
-Okay.
-Puna, step back!

41
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:15,440
Oops!

42
00:05:21,320 --> 00:05:22,800
PROCESSED AGRICULTURAL PRODUCTS

43
00:05:32,400 --> 00:05:33,280
Sorry.

44
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:54,200
UNINSPECTED, DO NOT OPEN!

45
00:05:56,080 --> 00:05:57,120
Hey, Manat!

46
00:06:00,080 --> 00:06:01,280
UNINSPECTED, DO NOT OPEN!

47
00:06:01,360 --> 00:06:02,680
Chaiya.

48
00:06:03,400 --> 00:06:05,400
-Yes, Mr. Sonrak.
-Yes?

49
00:06:05,480 --> 00:06:06,680
Has Puna arrived yet?

50
00:06:06,760 --> 00:06:08,200
Not yet.

51
00:06:09,080 --> 00:06:10,320
I haven't seen her either.

52
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:16,680
Where's she gone? What will you do?
The extras playing villagers are ready.

53
00:06:18,160 --> 00:06:20,720
Well, we could shoot the villagers first.

54
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:24,240
Maybe we should go straight to scene two?

55
00:06:25,280 --> 00:06:26,560
Yeah, that works.

56
00:06:28,480 --> 00:06:30,200
It's up to you. Hurry and get it done.

57
00:06:31,200 --> 00:06:32,040
Okay, let's go.

58
00:06:42,640 --> 00:06:45,280
AGRICULTURAL PRODUCT PROCESSING FACTORY

59
00:06:49,720 --> 00:06:51,280
Hey, that's Mr. Sonrak!

60
00:06:51,360 --> 00:06:52,520
PROCESSED AGRICULTURAL PRODUCTS

61
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:56,120
You're right! Let's hurry inside.

62
00:06:59,480 --> 00:07:00,680
Oh no! We're dead!

63
00:07:00,760 --> 00:07:03,480
What? Who's dead? Where?

64
00:07:03,560 --> 00:07:05,400
It's us! We're the ones in trouble!

65
00:07:05,480 --> 00:07:07,760
Calm down! Think clearly, then tell me!

66
00:07:11,920 --> 00:07:15,920
Mr. Sonrak called Puna's phone.

67
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:17,560
What do we do, Miss Maria?

68
00:07:19,320 --> 00:07:20,520
What should we do?

69
00:07:20,600 --> 00:07:23,520
I don't know! Help me think!
Why are you asking me alone?

70
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:25,040
Why isn't she answering?

71
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:31,040
It's quiet now. Let's hurry inside.

72
00:07:31,120 --> 00:07:32,120
-Come on.
-Let's go.

73
00:07:34,280 --> 00:07:35,560
Miss Maria!

74
00:07:36,160 --> 00:07:40,320
It's ringing again. Mr. Sonrak
keeps calling Puna's phone!

75
00:07:40,400 --> 00:07:41,560
Oh no!

76
00:07:41,640 --> 00:07:45,160
Listen. I'll answer it and change
my voice to sound like Puna.

77
00:07:45,240 --> 00:07:48,120
Hello, Mr. Sonrak! Are you okay?
Have you eaten yet?

78
00:07:48,200 --> 00:07:49,080
That should settle it.

79
00:07:49,160 --> 00:07:51,120
Yeah, good. No!

80
00:07:51,960 --> 00:07:53,240
That will be the end of us.

81
00:07:53,320 --> 00:07:56,240
If you try to sound like Puna,
he will catch you.

82
00:07:56,320 --> 00:07:57,280
So what now?

83
00:07:57,360 --> 00:08:00,000
Just pretend you're the one
who found her phone.

84
00:08:00,640 --> 00:08:04,440
What if he comes to get the phone back?
What will you say?

85
00:08:05,200 --> 00:08:06,200
That's true.

86
00:08:06,280 --> 00:08:08,440
Well, then…

87
00:08:08,520 --> 00:08:10,800
Ugh! Just let it ring like that.

88
00:08:11,760 --> 00:08:14,560
What if someone hears the phone ringing?
What do we do, Miss Maria?

89
00:08:15,440 --> 00:08:16,440
Just put it on silent!

90
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:19,000
Yeah, good point.

91
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:22,640
Right! Why couldn't you think
of such a simple solution, Joey?

92
00:08:22,720 --> 00:08:25,440
You couldn't think of it either, Sophie.

93
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:29,840
Ugh! Let's hurry inside already!
You guys are talking too much.

94
00:08:29,920 --> 00:08:32,200
I might miss my chance
to be the lead in the commercial.

95
00:08:32,280 --> 00:08:33,919
Go get the stuff from the trunk!

96
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:39,880
-Hurry up!
-I'm hurrying!

97
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:42,400
So much stuff!

98
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:43,400
Put it away.

99
00:08:46,440 --> 00:08:47,400
Let's go!

100
00:08:53,920 --> 00:08:56,400
Hurry, Puna. They must
be waiting for us by now.

101
00:08:56,480 --> 00:08:58,160
-Let's go. This way!
-Hurry!

102
00:08:59,680 --> 00:09:00,920
AGRICULTURAL PRODUCT PROCESSING FACTORY

103
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:03,160
PROCESSED AGRICULTURAL PRODUCTS

104
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:05,360
Wong, you're handsome!

105
00:09:06,760 --> 00:09:09,440
Wait, don't you think
Sis Haan put on makeup

106
00:09:09,520 --> 00:09:10,480
just to prank us?

107
00:09:10,560 --> 00:09:12,320
No, she did not.
This is how a star does it.

108
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:13,320
Alright.

109
00:09:14,320 --> 00:09:16,080
We'll be shooting some stock shots.

110
00:09:16,160 --> 00:09:18,240
You guys keep packing the products.

111
00:09:18,320 --> 00:09:21,720
Don't stiffen up or look at the camera.
Just act naturally.

112
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:24,080
Got it. Hey, come here!

113
00:09:33,320 --> 00:09:35,200
Ready and…

114
00:09:36,280 --> 00:09:37,440
action!

115
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:41,080
AGRICULTURAL PRODUCT PROCESSING FACTORY

116
00:10:00,840 --> 00:10:03,280
Didn't the director tell you?
Don't stiffen up!

117
00:10:04,360 --> 00:10:08,440
Hey, man. We're on TV!

118
00:10:08,520 --> 00:10:11,320
-Will my family recognize me?
-Of course, you're on TV!

119
00:10:13,960 --> 00:10:16,040
Okay, cut.

120
00:10:16,120 --> 00:10:17,160
Passed.

121
00:10:17,240 --> 00:10:20,640
PROCESSED AGRICULTURAL PRODUCTS

122
00:10:25,760 --> 00:10:29,200
Chang, go back to the company
and see if Puna is still there.

123
00:10:30,520 --> 00:10:34,160
Mr. Sonrak, aren't you worrying
about her too much?

124
00:10:35,280 --> 00:10:36,640
She'll be here soon.

125
00:10:40,840 --> 00:10:43,960
Chang, listen carefully,
and remember this.

126
00:10:44,040 --> 00:10:47,360
For me, there's no such thing
as worrying too much about Puna. Got it?

127
00:10:48,480 --> 00:10:51,440
Go back and call me
as soon as you find out! Go!

128
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:53,440
Yes.

129
00:10:57,800 --> 00:11:02,600
Hi! I brought some snacks
to visit the set.

130
00:11:02,680 --> 00:11:04,560
Thank you. That's very kind of you.

131
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:10,520
Sophie, Joey, give the snacks to the crew.
It'll give them energy to work!

132
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:13,880
Got it. Here, snacks for everyone!

133
00:11:16,520 --> 00:11:20,240
Maria, have you seen Puna anywhere?

134
00:11:20,880 --> 00:11:21,720
Is something wrong?

135
00:11:23,520 --> 00:11:27,360
Before coming here,
I heard Puna talking on the phone

136
00:11:27,440 --> 00:11:31,640
with someone named Boss Nok.
Looks like he was coming to pick her up.

137
00:11:34,360 --> 00:11:36,000
Oh, Boss Nok?

138
00:11:36,080 --> 00:11:38,240
Yes. A few days ago,

139
00:11:38,320 --> 00:11:42,280
I saw her leaving Boss Nok's music label.
But I don't know what she went there for.

140
00:11:42,360 --> 00:11:44,840
I even took a photo.

141
00:11:44,920 --> 00:11:47,120
-Sophie! The photo.
-Yes?

142
00:11:47,200 --> 00:11:48,360
-The photo from that day.
-Yes.

143
00:11:49,280 --> 00:11:50,160
Joey!

144
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:53,040
-The phone.
-Huh?

145
00:11:53,120 --> 00:11:53,960
What?

146
00:11:56,280 --> 00:11:59,960
-Here! Proof! You can see it clearly.
-Yes.

147
00:12:00,040 --> 00:12:02,200
We really didn't frame Puna.

148
00:12:07,560 --> 00:12:09,480
If someone isn't loyal,

149
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:14,920
don't support them.

150
00:12:17,600 --> 00:12:18,920
Change the actor.

151
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:21,400
-Dad, I think…
-Maria.

152
00:12:22,440 --> 00:12:24,440
Are you ready to shoot this commercial?

153
00:12:28,600 --> 00:12:29,640
I'm ready!

154
00:12:32,400 --> 00:12:36,640
Kamnan, I'd like to have Maria
act in this commercial instead.

155
00:12:36,720 --> 00:12:38,960
Fine, do whatever you want.

156
00:12:52,280 --> 00:12:55,120
No cars at all, Teacher.

157
00:12:55,200 --> 00:12:57,760
Yeah, no idea where we are right now.

158
00:12:58,280 --> 00:13:00,080
Our phone was stolen too.

159
00:13:00,720 --> 00:13:02,320
We have to find a car somehow.

160
00:13:02,400 --> 00:13:06,920
Let's walk a bit further.
Maybe we'll find a car or some locals.

161
00:13:08,360 --> 00:13:10,960
Yeah, but what do we do?

162
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:13,640
There's still no car.

163
00:13:16,920 --> 00:13:20,240
Here it is! Excuse me!

164
00:13:20,320 --> 00:13:21,560
Hey! Excuse me!

165
00:13:23,760 --> 00:13:24,640
Wait!

166
00:13:30,960 --> 00:13:35,680
Hello! Do you happen to know
Kamnan Pong's factory?

167
00:13:35,760 --> 00:13:37,200
Yes, I know.

168
00:13:37,280 --> 00:13:39,160
Are you Teacher Mueangphrai?

169
00:13:39,240 --> 00:13:40,600
Yes, that's right.

170
00:13:40,680 --> 00:13:45,760
Oh, perfect! Could you take us
to Kamnan Pong's factory?

171
00:13:45,840 --> 00:13:48,440
Sure. I'm heading that way anyway.

172
00:13:48,520 --> 00:13:50,280
-Hop in!
-Perfect. We're in a rush.

173
00:13:50,360 --> 00:13:51,840
-Let's go.
-Thank you!

174
00:13:51,920 --> 00:13:52,760
Let's get in, teacher.

175
00:13:56,640 --> 00:13:58,040
Thank you so much!

176
00:14:04,960 --> 00:14:07,960
Right now, I've sent Chang to find Puna.

177
00:14:08,560 --> 00:14:13,360
As for you, do whatever you can.
Shoot whichever scenes you can first.

178
00:14:13,440 --> 00:14:15,440
I'll try to reach Puna by phone.

179
00:14:16,400 --> 00:14:20,280
-But she's already been replaced.
-If Maria hasn't gone on set yet,

180
00:14:20,360 --> 00:14:23,680
I still have the right
to put her back in. Understand?

181
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:26,200
Yes, I'll buy some time.

182
00:14:26,800 --> 00:14:28,920
Don't try any tricks like this, Sonrak.

183
00:14:30,160 --> 00:14:31,760
I know what you're thinking.

184
00:14:32,800 --> 00:14:36,440
Dad, I think Maria isn't suitable
for this commercial.

185
00:14:36,520 --> 00:14:39,160
I'll make her suitable.

186
00:14:39,240 --> 00:14:42,320
I'll have you act in the commercial
alongside Maria.

187
00:14:43,120 --> 00:14:44,480
Whoa, Dad!

188
00:14:46,400 --> 00:14:48,840
-Add lines to the script?
-Yes.

189
00:14:49,720 --> 00:14:54,960
Can you write extra lines to put Sonrak
in the commercial with Maria?

190
00:15:00,960 --> 00:15:01,800
Yes.

191
00:15:02,400 --> 00:15:03,920
Then do it this way.

192
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:05,520
Dad.

193
00:15:16,160 --> 00:15:18,600
AGRICULTURAL PRODUCT PROCESSING FACTORY

194
00:15:19,680 --> 00:15:21,360
Thank you so much!

195
00:15:25,040 --> 00:15:27,080
-Let's hurry inside, Teacher.
-Let's go.

196
00:15:29,640 --> 00:15:33,440
Ready, everyone? Action!

197
00:15:36,840 --> 00:15:39,320
AGRICULTURAL PRODUCT PROCESSING FACTORY

198
00:15:59,640 --> 00:16:01,080
Cut!

199
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:09,440
Who do you think you are,
showing up this late?

200
00:16:09,520 --> 00:16:13,120
Everyone's been waiting for hours!
Where have you been wandering?

201
00:16:15,440 --> 00:16:16,640
I was being set up.

202
00:16:16,720 --> 00:16:18,320
Don't make excuses.

203
00:16:22,120 --> 00:16:24,600
I don't like people who are irresponsible.

204
00:16:26,760 --> 00:16:28,000
Get out!

205
00:16:28,080 --> 00:16:30,000
Really, I was being set up.

206
00:16:30,080 --> 00:16:31,400
I said, get out!

207
00:16:31,480 --> 00:16:34,560
Dad! Calm down. Please listen to Puna.

208
00:16:34,640 --> 00:16:35,880
Stop defending her.

209
00:16:38,200 --> 00:16:40,400
Just do your job properly. Go!

210
00:16:41,720 --> 00:16:44,760
Well, Kamnan…

211
00:16:44,840 --> 00:16:46,480
Could you give Puna one more chance?

212
00:16:47,680 --> 00:16:48,560
Sonrak.

213
00:16:50,160 --> 00:16:52,640
Puna brought this on herself.

214
00:16:53,800 --> 00:16:55,240
I can't help with that.

215
00:17:00,080 --> 00:17:01,280
Get back on set.

216
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:10,520
What are you waiting for?
Finish the shoot!

217
00:18:15,680 --> 00:18:17,240
Hey! What's going on?

218
00:18:22,480 --> 00:18:23,800
Get down!

219
00:18:50,200 --> 00:18:51,280
Call the local police!

220
00:18:51,360 --> 00:18:52,840
Got it, honey.

221
00:19:05,640 --> 00:19:07,520
-Hey, fall back!
-Let's go!

222
00:19:12,160 --> 00:19:14,080
Hey, Pleaw!

223
00:19:14,160 --> 00:19:15,000
Ugh!

224
00:19:16,400 --> 00:19:17,440
Go!

225
00:19:22,080 --> 00:19:24,720
You're finished, Pleaw!

226
00:19:26,440 --> 00:19:29,000
Chit, move the stuff quickly!

227
00:19:29,080 --> 00:19:31,200
Yes, Boss! Let's go!

228
00:19:31,280 --> 00:19:32,520
Go!

229
00:19:32,600 --> 00:19:34,320
Let's go!

230
00:19:49,160 --> 00:19:50,640
Good to see you, Captain.

231
00:19:51,480 --> 00:19:54,600
Lucky you're here.
Otherwise, we'd be in big trouble.

232
00:19:54,680 --> 00:19:57,640
Who are the attackers? What do they want?

233
00:19:59,480 --> 00:20:04,840
Not sure, but probably competitors
who saw our factory doing well

234
00:20:04,920 --> 00:20:07,160
and sent people to mess things up.

235
00:20:09,760 --> 00:20:10,920
How many of them?

236
00:20:11,520 --> 00:20:14,480
That's probably for you to figure out.

237
00:20:24,680 --> 00:20:25,960
Mr. Sonrak! Blood!

238
00:20:27,960 --> 00:20:29,320
Sonrak! You're hit!

239
00:20:29,400 --> 00:20:32,080
-Don't pass out!
-Mr. Sonrak!

240
00:20:33,200 --> 00:20:35,280
Oh, you passed out?

241
00:20:35,360 --> 00:20:37,480
-Mr. Sonrak!
-Sonrak!

242
00:20:38,520 --> 00:20:41,760
Sonrak! Call an ambulance!

243
00:20:41,840 --> 00:20:42,920
Sonrak!

244
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:45,120
-Mr. Sonrak!
-Call an ambulance!

245
00:20:45,200 --> 00:20:47,720
I'll take him to the hospital.

246
00:20:47,800 --> 00:20:49,280
Hurry! Go quickly!

247
00:20:49,360 --> 00:20:51,240
Please help!

248
00:20:51,320 --> 00:20:52,520
Mr. Sonrak!

249
00:20:58,280 --> 00:21:00,880
Manat, stay here and deal with this!

250
00:21:02,120 --> 00:21:03,840
Sonrak! My son!

251
00:21:03,920 --> 00:21:05,080
Sophie!

252
00:21:05,160 --> 00:21:07,920
Yes, I'll check everything thoroughly.

253
00:21:08,640 --> 00:21:10,480
I'll prepare a report for you.

254
00:21:11,760 --> 00:21:12,920
Corporal.

255
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:13,840
Yes?

256
00:21:13,920 --> 00:21:18,160
There's a suspicious box in the factory
with Do Not Open labels.

257
00:21:18,240 --> 00:21:20,160
Get the captain to check it.

258
00:21:20,240 --> 00:21:23,040
But don't say it came from me.
I don't want any trouble.

259
00:21:23,120 --> 00:21:24,280
Where is the box?

260
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:26,880
Over there. I'll show you.

261
00:21:29,080 --> 00:21:30,360
PROCESSED AGRICULTURAL PRODUCTS

262
00:21:30,440 --> 00:21:31,280
Here it is.

263
00:21:42,760 --> 00:21:45,040
UNINSPECTED, DO NOT OPEN!

264
00:21:53,160 --> 00:21:54,840
There's a suspicious box inside, Captain.

265
00:21:55,520 --> 00:21:57,560
-Where is it?
-This way.

266
00:21:58,200 --> 00:21:59,160
Take me there.

267
00:22:12,360 --> 00:22:15,160
It's gone. The box is missing.

268
00:22:15,240 --> 00:22:16,520
It was just here a moment ago.

269
00:22:19,080 --> 00:22:20,040
Split up and search everywhere.

270
00:22:20,760 --> 00:22:22,440
If anyone finds anything,
report back to me.

271
00:22:22,520 --> 00:22:23,760
-Yes, sir.
-Yes.

272
00:22:36,200 --> 00:22:39,520
I've removed the bullet.
The initial check shows nothing serious,

273
00:22:39,600 --> 00:22:41,920
since no vital organs were hit.

274
00:22:43,720 --> 00:22:45,680
When will my son
be able to leave the hospital?

275
00:22:45,760 --> 00:22:48,040
I expect it will take about two weeks.

276
00:22:49,800 --> 00:22:51,840
That means his work
will have to be postponed.

277
00:22:52,880 --> 00:22:55,520
I agree. He needs to rest
and recover first.

278
00:22:55,600 --> 00:22:58,440
Don't overdo it,
or the wound could reopen.

279
00:22:59,040 --> 00:23:01,560
-I'll excuse myself now.
-Thank you, Doctor.

280
00:23:24,960 --> 00:23:26,120
How are you feeling, son?

281
00:23:26,200 --> 00:23:28,640
It hurts, Dad.

282
00:23:32,200 --> 00:23:36,520
The doctor said you need a long break.
No work for now.

283
00:23:37,160 --> 00:23:38,160
Yes, Dad.

284
00:23:41,160 --> 00:23:42,000
Dad.

285
00:23:43,800 --> 00:23:48,120
They attacked me again.
I remember they're Boss Noo's men.

286
00:23:48,200 --> 00:23:50,040
I remember, Dad.

287
00:23:51,520 --> 00:23:54,720
Yes, they won't stop causing trouble.

288
00:23:56,840 --> 00:24:01,520
I'm asking seriously, Dad.
Is there anything I don't know about?

289
00:24:05,920 --> 00:24:07,880
What do you mean by that question?

290
00:24:09,520 --> 00:24:13,320
I just want to know
if you're hiding something from me.

291
00:24:13,920 --> 00:24:15,560
But if not, I apologize, Dad.

292
00:24:19,680 --> 00:24:20,520
There isn't.

293
00:24:22,680 --> 00:24:25,800
Why don't we let the law handle them?

294
00:24:25,880 --> 00:24:29,720
Have the police deal with them,
or we could take them to court.

295
00:24:30,520 --> 00:24:34,480
I've got the police helping,
but they haven't managed anything yet.

296
00:24:35,560 --> 00:24:37,320
Then,

297
00:24:38,040 --> 00:24:40,640
should I go to the media?
The media might be able to help us.

298
00:24:41,680 --> 00:24:44,520
No! That'll only make things worse.

299
00:24:44,600 --> 00:24:48,840
Dad, we're being targeted.
We can't keep putting up with this.

300
00:24:55,640 --> 00:24:59,360
Let me find a way to deal with them.
You stay out of it.

301
00:25:01,240 --> 00:25:02,680
Then what are you going to do?

302
00:25:03,400 --> 00:25:08,200
I can handle this.
I don't want you getting involved.

303
00:25:09,480 --> 00:25:13,360
Fine, Dad. But you need
to end this quickly.

304
00:25:14,600 --> 00:25:16,240
It's affecting my work.

305
00:25:17,320 --> 00:25:18,560
I will.

306
00:25:23,840 --> 00:25:26,240
I'll end this problem
with Boss Noo very soon.

307
00:25:31,960 --> 00:25:36,320
Puna, your rice porridge looks delicious.

308
00:25:36,400 --> 00:25:39,120
Hopefully Sonrak will like it.

309
00:25:39,200 --> 00:25:43,080
Is it really okay, Teacher?
Should I really go visit Mr. Sonrak?

310
00:25:43,160 --> 00:25:45,240
Our goal is the teddy bear.

311
00:25:45,840 --> 00:25:47,840
You need to get close to Mr. Sonrak.

312
00:25:47,920 --> 00:25:50,720
Find a way into his house for that bear.

313
00:25:50,800 --> 00:25:53,320
So I'm supposed to be his girlfriend?

314
00:25:53,400 --> 00:25:55,680
You don't have to go that far.

315
00:25:55,760 --> 00:25:58,320
You just need a reason to go to his house,

316
00:25:58,400 --> 00:26:03,080
cook something for him,
and find a way inside.

317
00:26:03,840 --> 00:26:07,240
But I'm afraid Mr. Sonrak
might misunderstand

318
00:26:07,320 --> 00:26:08,880
and it could get out of hand.

319
00:26:08,960 --> 00:26:10,680
What choice do we have, Puna?

320
00:26:10,760 --> 00:26:12,840
If we don't do it,
there won't be any chance.

321
00:26:18,040 --> 00:26:19,440
-Let's go.
-Let's go.

322
00:26:23,400 --> 00:26:24,720
Puna.

323
00:26:26,680 --> 00:26:29,120
I'm so glad you came to visit me.

324
00:26:30,120 --> 00:26:32,120
I'm a company artist.

325
00:26:32,200 --> 00:26:36,440
After everything that happened with you,
it wouldn't be right if I didn't come.

326
00:26:39,200 --> 00:26:42,120
It's past mealtime.
Mr. Sonrak, have you eaten yet?

327
00:26:43,680 --> 00:26:46,440
No, it's fine. I'm not hungry yet.

328
00:26:46,520 --> 00:26:50,520
Oh really? I brought
some rice porridge. Should I…

329
00:26:50,600 --> 00:26:53,600
What? You made rice porridge for me?

330
00:26:54,600 --> 00:26:56,880
Perfect timing, Puna! I'm hungry.

331
00:26:56,960 --> 00:26:59,400
Go ahead and serve me, okay?

332
00:26:59,480 --> 00:27:01,520
-Sure. Just a moment.
-I'm hungry.

333
00:27:01,600 --> 00:27:02,920
Thank you.

334
00:27:07,240 --> 00:27:09,000
You get hungry fast, huh?

335
00:27:11,480 --> 00:27:14,920
Well, I haven't eaten anything
since this morning.

336
00:27:19,160 --> 00:27:22,480
DARATHONG MUSIC

337
00:27:37,720 --> 00:27:40,920
What are we waiting for?
We need to tell Mr. Singha first,

338
00:27:41,000 --> 00:27:42,480
before he hears it from them!

339
00:27:43,480 --> 00:27:44,520
Then let's go in together.

340
00:27:45,240 --> 00:27:47,360
-Joey, you lead.
-Huh?

341
00:27:48,480 --> 00:27:49,360
Why me?

342
00:27:49,440 --> 00:27:50,920
-What?
-Why me?

343
00:27:51,000 --> 00:27:53,080
-What?
-Why does it have to be me?

344
00:27:53,160 --> 00:27:56,080
You're big. If anyone gets pushed,
it'll be you first.

345
00:27:56,160 --> 00:27:57,040
-True.
-Go.

346
00:27:57,120 --> 00:27:58,720
-Lead the way?
-Yeah.

347
00:27:58,800 --> 00:27:59,960
Quickly!

348
00:28:00,040 --> 00:28:01,320
-Alright, fine.
-Go.

349
00:28:04,640 --> 00:28:05,600
Come in.

350
00:28:16,760 --> 00:28:18,960
-Hello.
-What's this about?

351
00:28:19,040 --> 00:28:23,760
Yesterday, Puna was late
to shoot the commercial

352
00:28:23,840 --> 00:28:25,520
because we caused the delay.

353
00:28:31,360 --> 00:28:32,720
How did it happen?

354
00:28:33,560 --> 00:28:39,000
The reason we held Puna back from filming
is because we found out

355
00:28:39,080 --> 00:28:43,520
she was planning to switch music labels.
It's the evidence we showed at the set.

356
00:28:46,240 --> 00:28:49,960
If you want to see it again,
we secretly recorded a clip.

357
00:28:51,480 --> 00:28:54,280
We were really angry that Puna

358
00:28:54,360 --> 00:28:56,400
betrayed Darathong Music,

359
00:28:56,480 --> 00:29:00,520
so we locked her up.
We didn't want her filming the commercial.

360
00:29:01,960 --> 00:29:04,840
That's right. If Puna
filmed the commercial

361
00:29:04,920 --> 00:29:08,560
and switched labels, it would clearly
be taking advantage of the company.

362
00:29:12,960 --> 00:29:15,920
I'm sorry for acting on my own.

363
00:29:16,000 --> 00:29:20,880
I was really angry at Puna. I don't want
a singer like that in our company.

364
00:29:35,640 --> 00:29:40,280
Ice, call Boss Nok from Bai Tong Music.

365
00:30:03,480 --> 00:30:06,320
Is it too bland?
I made it in a bit of a hurry.

366
00:30:08,280 --> 00:30:09,760
Not bland at all.

367
00:30:09,840 --> 00:30:12,520
It's just right, Puna. I really like it.

368
00:30:12,600 --> 00:30:15,560
Then eat it all,
so you can get better quickly.

369
00:30:16,800 --> 00:30:18,240
I don't want to get better.

370
00:30:18,960 --> 00:30:22,120
I want you to make this porridge
for me every day.

371
00:30:24,520 --> 00:30:29,960
If you want more of my cooking,
when you're better, I'll cook for you.

372
00:30:30,640 --> 00:30:31,840
Really?

373
00:30:32,520 --> 00:30:37,520
Yes, but if I make it at home
and bring it to the office,

374
00:30:37,600 --> 00:30:40,320
it might get a little cold.

375
00:30:40,400 --> 00:30:42,000
Then you can cook at my place too.

376
00:30:42,080 --> 00:30:44,720
But if she goes to cook at your house,

377
00:30:44,800 --> 00:30:48,720
I'll go along.
She doesn't want any gossips

378
00:30:49,440 --> 00:30:53,920
That's fine, Teacher.
When I get out of the hospital,

379
00:30:55,000 --> 00:30:56,600
Puna, you'll cook at my house, okay?

380
00:30:57,840 --> 00:30:58,680
Yes.

381
00:31:08,360 --> 00:31:09,280
Eat a lot, okay?

382
00:31:09,800 --> 00:31:12,160
DARATHONG MUSIC

383
00:31:13,440 --> 00:31:14,640
Wait, Boss!

384
00:31:14,720 --> 00:31:16,360
-What?
-Are you really going in?

385
00:31:16,440 --> 00:31:18,120
Yeah, why? What's it to you?

386
00:31:18,720 --> 00:31:20,520
I'm just worried

387
00:31:20,600 --> 00:31:23,280
something might happen.
But don't worry, Boss.

388
00:31:23,880 --> 00:31:25,560
If anything goes wrong,

389
00:31:26,280 --> 00:31:28,400
I'll take the bullets myself.

390
00:31:29,280 --> 00:31:32,360
Tu, last time,

391
00:31:32,440 --> 00:31:34,120
even a barking dog scared you

392
00:31:34,200 --> 00:31:36,440
and you ran hiding over there.

393
00:31:37,240 --> 00:31:39,360
-Is that right?
-Yes.

394
00:31:39,440 --> 00:31:40,920
-Move aside!
-Got it.

395
00:31:42,000 --> 00:31:45,520
Singha has a weakness. You'll see.

396
00:31:47,000 --> 00:31:49,520
We have to face each other one-on-one.

397
00:31:51,960 --> 00:31:55,280
Wake up, amulet. Trouble's coming!
Please wake up!

398
00:31:58,000 --> 00:31:59,240
No, don't follow her!

399
00:32:00,440 --> 00:32:01,280
Teacher.

400
00:32:01,880 --> 00:32:03,320
Hey, his room is that way!

401
00:32:05,800 --> 00:32:07,920
That's Boss Nok.

402
00:32:09,600 --> 00:32:13,560
Yes, he's probably here to talk about you.

403
00:32:13,640 --> 00:32:15,320
Let's go listen.

404
00:32:17,440 --> 00:32:18,800
SONRAK DARATHONG

405
00:32:18,880 --> 00:32:19,960
Calm down, Boss.

406
00:32:26,000 --> 00:32:26,840
We meet again.

407
00:32:28,120 --> 00:32:29,440
So glad to see you!

408
00:32:30,080 --> 00:32:32,360
Hello. Please, this way.

409
00:32:32,440 --> 00:32:35,840
Wait, seriously, from the heart,

410
00:32:35,920 --> 00:32:38,360
you're perfect!

411
00:32:38,440 --> 00:32:40,520
Do you want to be a singer?
I can train you.

412
00:32:40,600 --> 00:32:42,800
You have such an aura.

413
00:32:42,880 --> 00:32:44,040
It's really uplifting.

414
00:32:45,400 --> 00:32:46,600
What?

415
00:32:47,480 --> 00:32:49,880
-She's Kamnan Pong's secretary.
-Hey! What are you saying?

416
00:32:49,960 --> 00:32:52,240
If I train you,

417
00:32:52,920 --> 00:32:55,800
I could just look at your face all day.

418
00:32:56,560 --> 00:32:59,560
I really like your looks.

419
00:32:59,640 --> 00:33:04,880
Boss, you'll listen to her voice
all day and night, right?

420
00:33:04,960 --> 00:33:06,200
-That's right.
-Yeah, her voice!

421
00:33:06,280 --> 00:33:10,000
I'll listen to your voice
all day and night. I don't know why,

422
00:33:10,840 --> 00:33:13,560
but your charm, it just grabs my heart!

423
00:33:14,560 --> 00:33:18,240
Your face…

424
00:33:18,320 --> 00:33:19,640
-Tu.
-Yes?

425
00:33:20,480 --> 00:33:22,560
Isn't she Kamnan Pong's secretary?

426
00:33:22,640 --> 00:33:25,640
Why didn't you warn me?
You let me get lost in her charm.

427
00:33:26,160 --> 00:33:30,000
I've been saying it from the start!
My mouth's splitting, still not listening.

428
00:33:30,080 --> 00:33:32,400
You said she's beautiful.
I said she's his secretary.

429
00:33:32,480 --> 00:33:33,520
You're going to get shot!

430
00:33:33,600 --> 00:33:37,000
You said nothing! You left me dreamy.
It's embarrassing.

431
00:33:37,080 --> 00:33:38,440
-Everyone here saw it.
-Yeah.

432
00:33:38,520 --> 00:33:40,200
Boss Nok, you're in a good mood today?

433
00:33:40,280 --> 00:33:42,360
Oh, I'm in a good mood

434
00:33:43,040 --> 00:33:45,160
because I got to see your face.

435
00:33:46,840 --> 00:33:47,880
Please, this way.

436
00:33:47,960 --> 00:33:49,000
Where?

437
00:33:49,080 --> 00:33:50,640
Mr. Singha is waiting.

438
00:33:50,720 --> 00:33:54,360
Fine, let's go. You lead.

439
00:33:59,600 --> 00:34:01,080
Boss Nok is here, sir.

440
00:34:01,160 --> 00:34:02,320
Come in.

441
00:34:03,840 --> 00:34:08,239
SONRAK DARATHONG, MARIA DARATHONG

442
00:34:08,320 --> 00:34:09,440
Please have a seat.

443
00:34:14,440 --> 00:34:15,639
We need to talk.

444
00:34:18,120 --> 00:34:21,679
Yeah, that's why I came myself.

445
00:34:22,280 --> 00:34:24,320
About Puna.

446
00:34:27,639 --> 00:34:29,000
You're interested in my artist?

447
00:34:30,880 --> 00:34:31,719
Yes.

448
00:34:32,520 --> 00:34:35,199
I want to ask, if you didn't plan
to produce music for her…

449
00:34:38,679 --> 00:34:40,440
why trick her into signing a contract?

450
00:34:40,520 --> 00:34:41,360
DARATHONG MUSIC

451
00:34:42,840 --> 00:34:44,520
How did you know I tricked her?

452
00:34:44,600 --> 00:34:46,760
Everyone in the industry knows.

453
00:34:47,320 --> 00:34:51,639
I checked everything.
Everyone in the music industry says

454
00:34:51,719 --> 00:34:53,920
you didn't order a new song for Puna.

455
00:34:55,080 --> 00:34:57,680
I've been in this business forever.

456
00:34:58,440 --> 00:35:00,640
Everyone knows that if a company

457
00:35:00,720 --> 00:35:03,320
doesn't order a new song for a singer,

458
00:35:03,400 --> 00:35:05,480
it clearly means

459
00:35:06,320 --> 00:35:10,480
you're shelving them.

460
00:35:15,800 --> 00:35:16,640
I shelved her

461
00:35:18,760 --> 00:35:20,720
because I didn't think she'd be popular.

462
00:35:21,720 --> 00:35:24,400
Nowadays, sweet singers
just don't sell anymore.

463
00:35:30,440 --> 00:35:31,360
Puna.

464
00:35:35,120 --> 00:35:36,600
Poor Puna.

465
00:35:38,720 --> 00:35:41,480
The media's been reporting
everything to me.

466
00:35:41,560 --> 00:35:44,280
Darathong Music

467
00:35:44,920 --> 00:35:48,080
is pouring all its efforts
into promoting a singer

468
00:35:48,640 --> 00:35:50,080
named Maria.

469
00:35:50,160 --> 00:35:54,920
That means you have
high hopes for her, right?

470
00:35:56,280 --> 00:35:57,160
So what?

471
00:35:58,280 --> 00:35:59,440
Hey.

472
00:36:00,360 --> 00:36:02,960
Calm down.

473
00:36:03,560 --> 00:36:06,360
I come in peace. I just want to offer

474
00:36:06,440 --> 00:36:10,760
a chance to break the contract.

475
00:36:10,840 --> 00:36:13,280
That way, you could make more money

476
00:36:13,360 --> 00:36:17,680
and boost Maria's promotion.

477
00:36:17,760 --> 00:36:21,320
Why? Are you going to train this kid?

478
00:36:24,720 --> 00:36:29,600
Yes. I've liked her since the competition.

479
00:36:30,240 --> 00:36:34,520
It's a shame a talented kid like this
is being shelved.

480
00:36:34,600 --> 00:36:36,480
Are you sure

481
00:36:37,000 --> 00:36:40,120
you can make Puna famous if you take her?

482
00:36:41,120 --> 00:36:44,000
So far, I haven't seen your label
make anyone famous.

483
00:36:46,160 --> 00:36:48,040
Whether she becomes famous or not,

484
00:36:48,120 --> 00:36:49,640
that depends on the kid's luck.

485
00:36:50,720 --> 00:36:52,880
Let's be honest. How much are we talking?

486
00:36:57,560 --> 00:36:58,400
Ten million.

487
00:37:04,000 --> 00:37:05,720
Can you pay that?

488
00:37:06,440 --> 00:37:07,480
Ten million?

489
00:37:10,800 --> 00:37:12,280
I can't pay that.

490
00:37:14,440 --> 00:37:15,400
But I do have…

491
00:37:20,880 --> 00:37:24,800
photos showing your relationship
with Boss Noo.

492
00:37:30,200 --> 00:37:33,760
I also have videos of the conflicts
between you and him.

493
00:37:34,360 --> 00:37:37,600
And if these videos reach the police,

494
00:37:39,280 --> 00:37:41,000
everyone will understand

495
00:37:41,600 --> 00:37:45,040
what the conflict between you
and Boss Noo is really about.

496
00:37:58,560 --> 00:38:03,240
DARATHONG MUSIC

497
00:38:07,040 --> 00:38:10,480
<i>And the winner</i>
<i>of today's singing contest is…</i>

498
00:38:11,520 --> 00:38:15,160
<i>Puna, with the song</i>
<i>"Wait for Him to Forget".</i>

499
00:38:19,240 --> 00:38:19,960
DARATHONG COUNTRY MUSIC SINGING CONTEST

500
00:38:27,360 --> 00:38:30,240
Uncle, I won!

501
00:38:32,200 --> 00:38:34,040
My dream is finally coming true!

502
00:38:34,640 --> 00:38:38,040
Just a little more, dear.
You'll be an artist with your own songs.

503
00:38:39,800 --> 00:38:42,800
Your live voice,
anyone who hears it will fall in love.

504
00:39:13,640 --> 00:39:14,640
Teacher.

505
00:39:15,920 --> 00:39:19,280
Mr. Singha meant to shelve me.

506
00:39:21,800 --> 00:39:24,720
He never even ordered the composer

507
00:39:25,760 --> 00:39:27,800
to write me a song.

508
00:39:30,320 --> 00:39:34,600
He just tricked me into working for him
every single day.

509
00:39:35,280 --> 00:39:39,200
Now, you're officially an artist
under Darathong Music.

510
00:39:40,200 --> 00:39:42,800
From now on, you need
to be careful with your behavior.

511
00:39:42,880 --> 00:39:45,440
Don't do anything
that could damage the label's reputation.

512
00:39:47,880 --> 00:39:51,680
Thank you so much for giving me
the opportunity to follow my dream.

513
00:39:58,080 --> 00:40:01,120
Oh, what's this?

514
00:40:01,640 --> 00:40:05,400
Shelved like a jar of pickled food, huh?

515
00:40:07,400 --> 00:40:09,680
Poor thing, really pitiful.

516
00:40:09,760 --> 00:40:13,000
Hey, why feel sorry for her, Miss Maria?

517
00:40:13,080 --> 00:40:14,920
Some people are just luckier than others.

518
00:40:15,520 --> 00:40:19,040
That's true. She won the competition,

519
00:40:19,120 --> 00:40:21,520
but still hasn't had the chance
to sing a single song.

520
00:40:23,240 --> 00:40:26,720
Well, you two are exaggerating.

521
00:40:27,240 --> 00:40:30,880
But it's like this. Dirt is dirt.

522
00:40:32,160 --> 00:40:34,280
No matter how hard
you try to make it a star,

523
00:40:35,160 --> 00:40:38,000
no matter how high you climb,

524
00:40:38,600 --> 00:40:41,920
it will eventually fall back
to the ground.

525
00:40:44,920 --> 00:40:49,000
Is this the behavior of decent people,
mocking someone like this?

526
00:40:53,160 --> 00:40:54,680
Let them talk, Teacher.

527
00:40:56,760 --> 00:40:58,280
People like this have no filter.

528
00:41:03,880 --> 00:41:06,800
Don't think your words
will make me feel defeated.

529
00:41:12,240 --> 00:41:13,880
I may have no connections,

530
00:41:15,360 --> 00:41:17,680
no parents pushing me,

531
00:41:19,320 --> 00:41:22,600
but I have my voice. I have my dream.

532
00:41:25,120 --> 00:41:27,800
And I will never stop running.

533
00:41:31,600 --> 00:41:35,760
Then I'll just hope you can keep up.

534
00:41:44,320 --> 00:41:45,720
Keep going!

535
00:41:46,240 --> 00:41:47,560
We're cheering for you.

536
00:41:54,200 --> 00:41:55,120
Mr. Singha.

537
00:41:55,200 --> 00:41:56,280
Come here.

538
00:42:05,280 --> 00:42:06,320
Puna.

539
00:42:10,800 --> 00:42:12,760
I'm going to have you move
to Boss Nok's label.

540
00:42:18,680 --> 00:42:20,320
What does that mean?

541
00:42:21,840 --> 00:42:24,280
Boss Nok asked to take you in.

542
00:42:25,480 --> 00:42:27,560
He promises to make you famous.

543
00:42:29,200 --> 00:42:34,120
You have a great voice and potential,
so I want to give you the opportunity.

544
00:43:06,080 --> 00:43:08,000
That must be them.

545
00:43:56,040 --> 00:43:57,760
Uncle, is something wrong?

546
00:43:59,400 --> 00:44:01,800
-Is someone following us?
-Let's talk inside.

547
00:44:01,880 --> 00:44:03,560
-Okay.
-Let's go.

548
00:44:05,840 --> 00:44:10,200
What? Singha actually agreed
to let you sing at Boss Nok's label?

549
00:44:11,360 --> 00:44:15,800
Yes. I heard Boss Nok
offered a contract buyout,

550
00:44:15,880 --> 00:44:17,160
so Mr. Singha agreed.

551
00:44:19,320 --> 00:44:20,480
Does Aunt Wilai know about this?

552
00:44:21,720 --> 00:44:24,120
She does, and she agrees.

553
00:44:24,720 --> 00:44:27,400
It's a chance for me to have my own songs.

554
00:44:28,000 --> 00:44:31,920
Also, the bear
isn't at the company anymore,

555
00:44:32,840 --> 00:44:34,680
so there's no reason for me to stay there.

556
00:44:36,120 --> 00:44:38,640
Where did Singha put it?

557
00:44:39,440 --> 00:44:40,640
At his home, Uncle.

558
00:44:41,960 --> 00:44:46,680
Don't worry. I've set it up
with Mr. Sonrak to cook for him

559
00:44:46,760 --> 00:44:48,880
at his place on weekends.

560
00:44:49,560 --> 00:44:53,280
I plan to use that chance
to get the bear back.

561
00:44:53,360 --> 00:44:54,560
Puna.

562
00:44:55,480 --> 00:44:59,040
Going into the tiger's den
is even riskier than the company.

563
00:45:00,760 --> 00:45:02,240
I'm not going alone, Uncle.

564
00:45:02,320 --> 00:45:04,160
Teacher Mueangphrai is coming with me.

565
00:45:09,600 --> 00:45:12,880
Here's what we'll do. Whenever you go,

566
00:45:12,960 --> 00:45:14,960
I'll wait outside.

567
00:45:15,040 --> 00:45:18,080
If anything happens, call me.
I'll come in right away.

568
00:45:19,800 --> 00:45:20,920
Yes, Uncle.

569
00:45:31,120 --> 00:45:32,840
Mr. Sonrak, you're back.

570
00:45:32,920 --> 00:45:36,360
Aunt Riam, can you get
the medicine ready upstairs for me?

571
00:45:36,960 --> 00:45:38,280
-Sure.
-Thank you.

572
00:45:41,040 --> 00:45:42,120
Mr. Sonrak.

573
00:45:42,920 --> 00:45:45,000
I heard, right now,

574
00:45:45,080 --> 00:45:47,080
Boss Nok is setting up a room

575
00:45:47,160 --> 00:45:50,440
to welcome Puna as a new singer.

576
00:45:51,720 --> 00:45:52,720
What is going on?

577
00:45:52,800 --> 00:45:55,160
Puna's moving to Boss Nok's label.

578
00:45:57,920 --> 00:46:00,120
No way. I don't believe it. Where's Dad?

579
00:46:00,200 --> 00:46:01,200
I'm here.

580
00:46:03,880 --> 00:46:04,720
Dad.

581
00:46:06,200 --> 00:46:08,560
-What's happening?
-That's right.

582
00:46:09,480 --> 00:46:12,640
Tomorrow, Puna will move
to Boss Nok's label. Earlier today,

583
00:46:12,720 --> 00:46:14,520
my discussion with him was final.

584
00:46:14,600 --> 00:46:15,760
No, Dad!

585
00:46:16,280 --> 00:46:18,840
I won't allow it!
I won't let Puna go to him.

586
00:46:18,920 --> 00:46:20,200
I'll call him myself!

587
00:46:21,360 --> 00:46:22,400
Sonrak.

588
00:46:22,480 --> 00:46:23,800
What, Dad?

589
00:46:23,880 --> 00:46:25,680
I know how you feel about Puna.

590
00:46:25,760 --> 00:46:29,600
But listen, our company doesn't have
the budget to train her anymore.

591
00:46:29,680 --> 00:46:31,800
That's why I have to send her to Boss Nok.

592
00:46:31,880 --> 00:46:33,680
How can there be no budget?
I saw it myself!

593
00:46:33,760 --> 00:46:35,360
Kamnan Pong signed the approval.

594
00:46:40,520 --> 00:46:43,240
The budget's been used elsewhere.
There's nothing left for Puna.

595
00:46:46,480 --> 00:46:48,560
Used elsewhere? But that's Puna's budget!

596
00:46:49,160 --> 00:46:50,360
I spent the budget on you!

597
00:46:51,520 --> 00:46:54,880
You and Maria are trending as a ship,
so I have to keep it going.

598
00:46:54,960 --> 00:46:57,680
I need money to run events
to draw in fans.

599
00:46:57,760 --> 00:46:59,240
It all costs money.

600
00:47:01,400 --> 00:47:04,120
Come on. Don't worry.

601
00:47:04,200 --> 00:47:07,080
I won't let Puna go easily
like others think.

602
00:47:07,160 --> 00:47:09,960
So, you're using Boss Nok

603
00:47:10,040 --> 00:47:11,720
to train Puna?

604
00:47:12,840 --> 00:47:15,320
Yes, I have a plan.

605
00:47:16,080 --> 00:47:18,480
Wen she becomes popular,
I'll bring her back.

606
00:47:24,000 --> 00:47:27,080
Sonrak, don't worry.

607
00:47:27,160 --> 00:47:30,640
Even if Puna's at another label,
she's still in the same circle.

608
00:47:30,720 --> 00:47:33,680
She hasn't gone anywhere. I know…

609
00:47:34,880 --> 00:47:38,320
I know how you feel about her.
If you want to date her, I won't stop you.

610
00:47:38,400 --> 00:47:41,800
Just don't let the fans know yet. Got it?

611
00:47:44,400 --> 00:47:47,360
You just got back
from the hospital. Go rest.

612
00:47:48,160 --> 00:47:49,040
Chang.

613
00:47:49,640 --> 00:47:50,880
Take care of your boss.

614
00:47:54,480 --> 00:47:55,560
Leave me alone!

615
00:47:55,640 --> 00:47:56,760
Sonrak.

616
00:47:57,760 --> 00:47:58,600
Sonrak!

617
00:48:01,240 --> 00:48:03,960
SONRAK DARATHONG, MARIA DARATHONG

618
00:48:07,000 --> 00:48:11,480
Do you think I should get Puna
a mic keychain?

619
00:48:12,000 --> 00:48:12,840
It's cute, right?

620
00:48:14,840 --> 00:48:16,720
Are you spoiling girls now?

621
00:48:17,360 --> 00:48:19,680
Go for it! I support you.

622
00:48:20,640 --> 00:48:22,840
Maybe she'll finally accept you
as a boyfriend.

623
00:48:25,200 --> 00:48:28,960
Just a keychain,
can it really change a girl's mind?

624
00:48:29,040 --> 00:48:30,520
It's not spoiling.

625
00:48:31,040 --> 00:48:34,760
It's a subtle way to show your feelings,

626
00:48:35,520 --> 00:48:38,480
like water slowly seeping through sand.
You get it?

627
00:48:40,960 --> 00:48:42,640
Got it, Master.

628
00:48:42,720 --> 00:48:44,000
Hey, Ice is here.

629
00:48:44,080 --> 00:48:48,080
Ice, have you seen Puna?
Someone around here

630
00:48:48,680 --> 00:48:49,520
is looking for her.

631
00:48:49,600 --> 00:48:52,680
Puna? She's just packing up in her room.

632
00:48:52,760 --> 00:48:53,640
Packing up?

633
00:48:55,040 --> 00:48:57,240
-Yeah.
-Where is she going?

634
00:48:58,320 --> 00:49:00,040
Got an outside job today?

635
00:49:00,120 --> 00:49:01,840
Mr. Sonrak didn't say he had to go out.

636
00:49:03,080 --> 00:49:05,760
You two still don't know yet?

637
00:49:09,880 --> 00:49:10,800
Know what?

638
00:49:11,400 --> 00:49:15,560
Puna's moving to Boss Nok's label
as a singer.

639
00:49:17,520 --> 00:49:18,440
What?

640
00:49:22,320 --> 00:49:23,360
Puna.

641
00:49:24,240 --> 00:49:27,240
Whoa, wait. What's going on?

642
00:49:27,320 --> 00:49:28,840
DARATHONG MUSIC

643
00:49:33,320 --> 00:49:34,360
Puna!

644
00:49:40,280 --> 00:49:42,440
I hope you become the singer
you've dreamed of.

645
00:49:42,520 --> 00:49:46,680
NEXT EPISODE

646
00:49:47,280 --> 00:49:48,240
Just so you know,

647
00:49:49,160 --> 00:49:51,400
you two can't measure up to Puna.

648
00:49:52,600 --> 00:49:56,080
I want you to take
Captain Tom down. Got it?

649
00:49:58,280 --> 00:49:59,200
Move, now!

650
00:50:00,840 --> 00:50:02,160
-Sergeant!
-Sergeant!

651
00:50:02,240 --> 00:50:03,960
Hey! Chit, don't shoot! Stop!

652
00:52:02,080 --> 00:52:05,000
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
